Objective: Design a refactoring architecture for a Next.js 14 App Router + Supabase project

Context - Current codebase problems:
1. RoleRow/UserRoleRow types duplicated in 7 files with inconsistent fields (some have accounting_group_id, some dont; some allow arrays, some dont)
2. Auth+profile resolution pattern (createClient+getUser+extractStudentNumber+findProfileIdByStudentNumber) copy-pasted ~20 times across 8 action files
3. findProfileIdByStudentNumber in lib/account.ts accepts studentNumber param but IGNORES IT - just calls supabase.auth.getUser() again internally. So every call site does: getUser() -> extractStudentNumber() -> findProfileIdByStudentNumber() which calls getUser() AGAIN. The user.id is available from step 1.
4. verifyAdmin (app/admin/actions.ts) and checkManagePermission (app/members/manage/actions.ts) each create their own supabase client internally; their callers also create one. Total: ~14 wasted createClient() calls.
5. Japanese role name strings (会計, 部長, 副部長) hardcoded in 18+ locations; English role type strings (admin, accounting, leader, general) hardcoded 40+ times across 10 files.

Current file structure:
- lib/account.ts - createUserSchema, extractStudentNumberFromUser, findProfileIdByStudentNumber
- lib/teams.ts - getUserTeams (also defines local Role type)
- utils/supabase/server.ts - createClient(), createAdminClient()
- No types/ directory exists

Current auth pattern in most action files:
  const supabase = await createClient();
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
  if (!user) return { error: '認証が必要です' };
  const studentNumber = extractStudentNumberFromUser(user);
  const profileId = await findProfileIdByStudentNumber(supabase, studentNumber);
  if (!profileId) return { error: '認証が必要です' };

